commentary: Woakes to Williamson, OUT drops Williamson but it looks like he's got Santner with a fingertip! Surely. They've sent it upstairs but Santner isn't waiting. Oh what a terrible way to go. Santner has his bat high up, probably because it's a firm drive that he expects to come towards him. This means he has a longer distance down towards the crease. Woakes gets half a finger. Santner whacks himself on the pad after getting into the dressing room. That's the first time he's been dismissed in the series. Is that it for England?
